## Frontend Testing (TypeScript)

### Framework & Dependencies
- **Test Runner**: Vitest 2.x with `@testing-library/react>=16.0.0`
- **Component Testing**: `@testing-library/user-event>=14.5.0`
- **E2E (Optional)**: Playwright for critical user journeys
- **Coverage**: Minimum 75% for components, 90% for utilities

### Test Structure
```text
frontend/
├── __tests__/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── BriefingDashboard.test.tsx
│   │   ├── ObservabilityBadge.test.tsx
│   │   └── ConsentPromptModal.test.tsx
│   ├── hooks/
│   │   └── useBriefing.test.ts
│   └── utils/
│       └── sanitize.test.ts
```

### Required Test Patterns

```typescript
// REQUIRED: ARIA accessibility assertions
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { BriefingDashboard } from '@/components/BriefingDashboard';

describe('BriefingDashboard', () => {
  it('renders briefing content with proper accessibility', () => {
    render(<BriefingDashboard briefing="Test content" status="success" />);

    expect(screen.getByRole('article')).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByText('Test content')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });

  it('shows degraded state with retry option', () => {
    render(<BriefingDashboard briefing="" status="degraded" />);

    expect(screen.getByRole('alert')).toBeInTheDocument();
    expect(screen.getByRole('button', { name: /retry/i })).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

