## Test Suite Count Maintenance (MANDATORY)

When adding or removing test functions, classes, or parametrized cases under `backend/tests/`:

1. Run `uv run pytest --collect-only -q backend/tests` to get the new total
2. Update the `<!-- test-inventory:total=N -->` marker in every tracked doc:
   - `docs/SECURITY.md` (inventory table + marker)
   - `README.md` (badge, tech stack table, tree diagram, quick-start comments)
   - `backend/AGENT.md`
   - `AGENT.md`
   - `proposal-case-study.md`
3. Update any prose that cites the total test count (e.g. "1193 automated tests", `uv run pytest # N tests`)
4. Run `uv run pytest backend/tests/test_suite_inventory.py` — must pass before merge

Parametrized expansions (e.g. `@pytest.mark.parametrize` over `INJECTION_PAYLOADS`) change the collected total — update docs when those change too.

